CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 15, 1956, pg. A15, reads: "Admiring Art - Members of the Aurora Club held their Christmas party at the Pittsburgh Center for Art. Here four of the ladies listen to Mrs. J. Alfred Wilner, art director at the center, describe one piece of art.  Left to right: Miss Carolyn Lovett, Mrs. Frances Primas, Mrs. Wilner, Mrs. Lillian Brown and Mrs. Ethel Golden. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. J. Alfred Wilner third from left describing painting to Aurora Reading Club members from left: Carolyn Lovett, Frances Primas, (Mrs. Wilner), Lillian Brown, and Ethel Golden, in Pittsburgh Center for Art
